{
  "texts": [
    "These findings suggested that shutting down dark web marketplaces does not affect street crime permanently.",
    "It was hypothesized that street drug dealers could quickly use another dark web marketplace after one closes.",
    "Additionally, researchers suggested that street drug dealers could find other means of obtaining drugs, including buying them from other street dealers or growing them.According to researchers, ULMFit, Bert, and RoBERTa are pre-trained transferable models that could be used to classify illicit activities on the dark web [38].",
    "In comparison with traditional text classification methods such as LSTM, the researchers found that Bert obtained the best accuracy in classifying dark web drug content and types.",
    "The researcher approach is significant since law enforcement agencies can identify and track illicit activities on the dark web without manually labeling data."
  ]
}